   132	def run_b_sweep(smoke, graphs: dict, db_dir: Path, output: str) -> int:
   133	    """Follow-up implicated by the R6 placebo (length-norm penalty confirmed): sweep the
   134	    tunable BM25 `b` (length-normalization) over {plain, enriched} docs. Does lowering `b`
   135	    let enrichment's content gain net positive — and beat plain FathomDB-FTS (the FTS5 `b`
   136	    is fixed/un-tunable, so this also probes whether a tunable-`b` BM25 should replace it)?"""
