    29	
    30	---
    31	
    32	## 0. Goal (0.8.3) — the resolution gate
    33	
    34	**Reach `FathomDB − Mem0` ≥ −ε (near-parity) or > 0 (better) on the agentic-memory axis**, per memory
    35	class, under the identical answerer, with **eu7 ≥ 0.90 held** and **no latency-budget breach** —
    36	secondary comparator **Graphiti/Zep**. The resolution is achieved by closing the measured gap with the
    37	**fewest sufficient experiments**, then stopping at parity (or, on HITL choice, pursuing a surpass lever).
    38	
    39	### Two-level measurement (the key reframe)
    40	
    41	- **External — the resolution gate.** `FathomDB − {Mem0, Graphiti/Zep, naive-RAG}` per memory class
    42	  (factoid / knowledge_update / multi_session / temporal), identical-answerer, on the **re-pinned,
    43	  power-sized** gold corpus. This decides *done*.
    44	- **Internal — attribution only.** Each lever vs the corrected-fused baseline (the M1 comparator). Tells
    45	  us *which* lever closed the gap; it does not, by itself, mean the resolution is reached.
    46	
    47	Slice 0 freezes both in code (`eval/decision_rule_083.py`, extending `eval/m1_decision_rule.py`).
    48	
    49	### Goals → instruments
    50	
    51	| Goal | Instrument | Role |
    52	|---|---|---|
    53	| **Agentic-memory parity (resolution)** | identical-answerer accuracy + strict Recall@K vs **Mem0 / Graphiti-Zep / naive-RAG** on the re-pinned gold (non-zero gold on the 4 classes) | **GATE** (external) |
    54	| Exploratory recall | IR corpus eu8 relevance recall@10 | lever signal |
    55	| Deep-exploratory recall | IR corpus ~596-query hard subset (recall@10/@50, median rank) | lever signal |
    56	| Multi-hop QA | MuSiQue all-bridges@K (presence) **and** F1-given-all-bridges (composition) co-primary (ADJ-10); pooled ≥3-hop F1 confirmatory | lever signal |
    57	| System health (hard gate) | IR corpus **eu7 fidelity recall@10 ≥ 0.90** | BLOCK gate |
    58	| System health — latency (hard gate, ADJ-9) | AC012/AC013/AC020 re-measured on read-path slices | BLOCK gate |
    59	
    60	### Pre-registered decision rule (frozen at Slice 0)
    61	
    62	- **Resolution REACHED:** the external `FathomDB − Mem0` per-class delta clears the near-parity band on
    63	  the **power-sized** corpus (per-class MDE ≤ the parity tolerance; ADJ-1/ADJ-3 power discipline), eu7 ≥
    64	  0.90, latency intact. ⇒ **Present the surpass-option package; HITL signs "ship at parity" or "pursue
    65	  surpass."**
    66	- **Resolution NOT reached:** record the **residual gap + the named binding constraint** (most likely the
    67	  embedder ceiling or the reader), and the explicit fork — (a) carry a stronger embedder, (b) the
    68	  caller-side reader axis (out of the library footprint), or (c) a memory-class-specific lever. This
    69	  replaces the old "both-null fallback": 0.8.3 always ends in a *decision*, never an open redirect.
    70	- **Internal attribution** (lever vs corrected-fused, MDE-feasible materiality — the M1 rule was
    71	  underpowered even at N=1165) is reported per lever so the gap-closure is explainable.
    72	
    73	---
    74	
    75	## 1. What "fair" requires (carried from M1 + the capability report)
    76	
    77	- **Identical-answerer, same depth, one corpus.** Adapters expose only `retrieve(question, k)`; one
    78	  answerer / one prompt / one context budget across FathomDB, Mem0, Graphiti/Zep, naive-RAG — so any
    79	  delta is retrieval, not prompt divergence (the R2 invariant). Reader = `gpt-5.4` (M1-proven), the one
    80	  priced EVAL-ONLY seam; cheap-validate (`gemini-2.5-flash-lite`) before any priced run.
    81	- **Power before claims (ADJ-1/ADJ-3).** The base-retrieval study had per-class MDE ≈21pp at n=160 — too
    82	  coarse for 5–7.5pp class deltas. Slice 0 sizes per-class N so **MDE ≤ the parity tolerance**; D0a must
    83	  hit that N per class (escalate the source if it can't). No parity claim on an under-powered class.
    84	- **eu7 re-clear is a HARD gate (ADJ-3).** Any embedder/pooling change rewrites the stored vectors; the
    85	  1-bit index must re-pass **eu7 ≥0.90** (point 0.896, CI-hi 0.925 today). A floor breach is **BLOCK →
    86	  HITL**, even if relevance improves. The unbisected 0.937→0.896 vector-path regression is bisected here.
    87	- **Embedder is a first-class lever, not a contingency (ADJ-6).** Dense is embedder-bound (eu8 ceiling
    88	  ≈0.571; fused *ties* BM25). So the $0 embedder probe is **primary**: it selects the lever, and PRF is
    89	  secondary. **Re-embed once** on the chosen embedder (CLS-correct), re-clear eu7 once — no double-jeopardy.
    90	- **Composition co-primary (ADJ-10).** Dense gets bridges more often (0.68 vs 0.65) but composes worse
    91	  (0.464 vs 0.552); a lever that wins presence but loses composition is **not** progress.
    92	- **Cheap-validate-before-ENGINE (ADJ-7).** No schema migration / in-engine read-path lever is built
    93	  until its $0 LLM-free gate passes (embedder probe before the re-embed/PRF build; D2 content-at-scale
    94	  proxy before the fielded-FTS migration). A failed gate ⇒ the engine slice does not run; record it.
    95	- **D2 placebo discipline.** A length-matched foreign-token placebo separates lexical-bridge *content*
    96	  value from the length artifact; fielded indexing keeps enrichment tokens out of the body channel.
    97	- **Latency is a fairness axis (ADJ-9).** Read-path changes re-measure AC012/AC013/AC020; a breach blocks
    98	  promotion (→ HITL), same as eu7.
