   102	## 2. Cross-cutting Definition of Done (binds every slice)
   103	
   104	- **Footprint invariant:** CPU-only, no-API at the library boundary, 1-bit-safe, deterministic. Offline
   105	  extraction = local Qwen3.6-27B ($0). The answerer is the one priced, EVAL-ONLY seam. Every technique is
   106	  tagged **IN-LIBRARY / CALLER-SIDE BYO-LLM / OFFLINE-BUILD / EVAL-ONLY**; no in-library LLM.
   107	- **X1 / X2 / X3 (engine slices):** surface/behavior/schema changes land in **both** Python and
   108	  TypeScript bindings + a live functional harness (X1); `mkdocs build` green (X2); `docs/` + DOC-INDEX in
   109	  the closing commit (X3).
   110	- **Determinism pins:** RRF byte-deterministic; fielded/weighted fusion + custom ranking **extend, never
   111	  weaken** the pins; PRF deterministic (bounded, fixed expansion).
   112	- **Schema:** the fielded-FTS channel is additive + `SCHEMA_VERSION` bump + EXPLAIN index-driven (no
   113	  SCAN/temp-B-tree) per the 0.8.1 Slice-33 precedent.
   114	- **Budget discipline ([[0.8.1-budget-discipline-cheap-validate-and-ledger]]):** cheap-validate before any
   115	  priced run; strong reader = `gpt-5.4`; $ ledger in `runs/STATUS-0.8.3.md`; **the three priced runs
   116	  (parity, D1 confirmatory, D2 confirmatory) are budgeted in aggregate at Slice 0**.
   117	- **Resilient priced runs ([[priced-runs-need-resilience-before-spend]]):** reuse M1's resilient harness
   118	  (auto-resume, atomic checkpoint, 429/5xx backoff, failure≠abstention, completeness validity guard).
   119	- **Latency-regression gate (ADJ-9):** every engine / read-path slice (20; 25) and the final stack (30)
   120	  re-measures AC012/AC013/AC020; a breach is a **BLOCK → HITL**.
   121	- **Surpass-option discipline:** at every Phase-B gate the orchestrator records whether a credible
   122	  surpass-Mem0 lever exists; the Slice-30 sign-off package presents it.
   123	- **Pre-registration + reviews:** endpoints + rule frozen as code before data; design reviewed; codex §9
   124	  on every slice before a verdict is recorded; cross-check green claims vs printed numbers
   125	  ([[background-exit-masks-real-exit]]).
