   130	
   131	```
   132	0  Design + pre-register the resolution gate (two-level), power-sized N, $0-probe criteria,
   133	   eu7-break fork, surpass-option protocol, F5/tunable-b scope ruling
   134	        │
   135	   PHASE A — establish the target (the gap IS the spine)
   136	        │
   137	5  D0a: power-sized gold re-pin (non-zero gold on the 4 classes) + answerer seam
   138	       + Mem0-OSS DE-RISK SPIKE & stand-up  (diagnose the prior blocker first)
   139	        │
   140	10 D0b: measure FathomDB − {Mem0, Graphiti/Zep, naive-RAG} per-class gap = THE TARGET
   141	        │
   142	   PHASE B — close the gap, cheapest-sufficient lever first, re-measure vs Mem0, STOP at parity
   143	        │
   144	15 $0 triage probes (LLM-free, no engine change):  15a embedder-ceiling (PRIMARY lever pick)
   145	                                                    ∥ 15b D2 content-at-scale proxy
   146	        │
   147	20 D1 build: CLS-fix + CHOSEN embedder (one re-embed) + one eu7 re-clear + corrected baseline
   148	       + deterministic vector PRF (only if the embedder alone leaves a gap) → re-measure vs Mem0
   149	       [eu7-break → fidelity-recovery fork + 0.937→0.896 bisect]   ←── may already reach parity → §surpass
   150	        │
   151	25 D2 build (only if 15b passed AND a gap remains): fielded-FTS/BM25F + tunable-b engine
   152	       + offline enrichment keys + length-matched placebo → re-measure vs Mem0
   153	        │
   154	30 RESOLUTION verdict: final FathomDB − {Mem0, Zep} per-class; parity reached?
   155	       + the SURPASS-OPTION package → HITL signs "ship at parity" or "pursue surpass"
   156	```
   157	
   158	**Stop-at-parity:** if Slice 20 already reaches near-parity-or-better, Slice 25 (D2) is **not run for
   159	completeness** — it runs only if a gap remains (or as a surpass lever the HITL elects). Levers are ordered
   160	by expected gap-closure × cheapness: embedder (highest-leverage per the report) → PRF → fielded enrichment.
