dev/plans/runs/0.7.2-PR-8-output.json:117:  "campaign_narrative": "0.7.2 closes the RELEASE-HARDENING campaign. Phase A took the held 0.7.0+0.7.1 work to a published, validated release: doc-drift sweep (PR-1), embedder concurrency hardening (PR-9), recall-floor reframe (PR-2 family — the 'gap' was a measurement artifact; ANN-fidelity 0.937, 0.90 floor holds), tiered real-corpus latency budget (PR-3), and the 0.7.1 publish (PR-4). Phase B hardened the test/perf foundation for the 0.8.x agent-memory work: corpus-driven test harness (PR-5), always-on dev-loop perf gates (PR-6), append-only perf-regression detection (PR-7). fathomdb 0.7.2 is the post-1.0-foundation cut. CAMPAIGN CLOSED."
