dev/plans/runs/GA-1-corpus-ab-20260608T012503Z-output.json:19:  "eu7_path_identical_detail": "The eu7 HARNESS measure_recall (exclude-before+dedup GT, RECALL_SEARCH_SLACK=5, set_search_limit_for_test) is BYTE-IDENTICAL between v0.7.2 and slice-40, and the dual-method+seam fixes (26b2f95, 5b69568) landed before the 0.937 json was written, so both anchors used the same harness method. BUT the production engine.search() path that eu7 measures CHANGED across 11 lib.rs commits v0.7.2..slice-40 — notably d28d204 (G9 RRF fusion made UNCONDITIONAL + rerank seam + G10 filtered-KNN + G12 recency) and 3e5ae59 (G1 SearchHit + step-11 FTS5 tokenizer upgrade). So the two anchor numbers are NOT a clean same-code comparison: 0.8.0 search() is RRF-fused hybrid, while eu7 ground truth is the pure exact-f32 VECTOR top-10.",
