dev/plans/runs/0.8.1-slice-30-option3-output.json:124:      "note": "s_cleaned WITH ELPS+graph arm. 26/200 ELPS extractions failed (LLM returned truncated JSON; per-doc exception caught, empty result returned). Graph arm effect vs baseline: temporal=0.0, knowledge_update=-0.0128, multi_session=0.0, factoid=0.0. Graph arm has no positive effect on recall. Root cause: entity nodes from ELPS don't carry source_doc_id in SearchHit — doc_id_of lambda falls back to str(sh.id) (integer row ID) which never matches gold session IDs. Entity node hits inject noise into RRF ranking."
dev/plans/runs/0.8.1-slice-30-option3-output.json:143:    "interpretation": "FathomDB dense+FTS fusion beats BM25 on multi_session (+1.5pp) but trails on temporal (-6pp) and knowledge_update (-5pp) against NaiveRAG. The graph arm provides zero positive recall benefit over FTS+dense alone. Root cause: entity nodes from graph arm retrieval don't resolve to source session IDs in the current doc_id_of mapping — SearchHit.id for entity nodes is the integer row ID, not the source_doc_id. Entity node hits inject noise into RRF without contributing matching doc_ids. The graph arm is architecturally implemented and the ELPS extraction pipeline works (harness speaks the protocol correctly, entities+edges are written to the graph), but the read path cannot recover source session IDs from entity node hits. Fix required: expose source_doc_id on SearchHit for graph arm entity node hits, or filter entity-node hits in FathomDBAdapter before computing RRF."
