dev/plans/runs/0.8.2-slice-20-resilience-output.json:59:      "description": "test_m1_power_sim.py has 3 PRE-EXISTING failing tests on this slice's baseline (028f387d): test_simulate_p_go_uses_real_decide_and_returns_probability, test_p_go_is_monotone_increasing_in_n_under_flat_positive, test_decide_is_the_real_frozen_rule. Verified by stashing this slice's changes and re-running — they fail identically on the unmodified baseline. Root cause is the decide()/MATERIAL_F1_LIFT threshold drift owned by the separate (unmerged, escalated) 0.8.2-pwrfix branch, NOT this slice. This slice touches neither decide() nor power_sim.",
