dev/plans/runs/0.7.2-PR-3-output.json:75:        "reason": "The synthetic isotropic fixture CANNOT meet max(baseline_p99*10,150ms) — a property of the synthetic DATA, not the box (clean-box loadavg ~2.6). Instant embed -> baseline 16-28ms -> bound 168-282ms, far tighter than production's 405ms; absolute 8-thread tail ~520ms@384d / ~1048ms@768d is the same order as the real path. K=64->192 (recall fix) raised the tail vs the old STATUS-PVQ 131ms (K=64).",
dev/plans/runs/0.8.0-slice-6-output.json:16:    "instruments": "real ac_012 (authoritative gate-level, coarse power-of-two percentile_ceil) + a throwaway SLICE6_EXPERIMENT-gated FTS-path harness (faithful SQL + byte-identical corpus, finer sorted percentiles) + one temporary-and-reverted engine-level A/B edit",
dev/plans/runs/0.8.0-slice-6-output.json:31:    "quality_proxy": "8 morphology/diacritic queries [run running ran optimize cafe naive resume connect]: CURRENT=8/8; porter unicode61=8/8; unicode61(+rd2)=5/8 (loses stemming run/optimize/connect); unicode61[≈v0.7.2]=5/8; porter ascii=5/8 (loses diacritics cafe/naive/resume); ascii=2/8. Porter buys morphological recall; diacritic folding (already in unicode61 default rd=1) buys accent-insensitivity. So the Slice-5 INCREMENTAL FTS-quality gain over v0.7.2 default unicode61 is specifically porter stemming."
dev/plans/runs/0.8.0-slice-6-output.json:33:  "q3_cost_attribution": "Cost tracks RESULT-SET SIZE, not tokenization. @100k current tokenizer: 1-token query matches ~3212 rows -> p50 3.93ms; 2-token AND -> ~2 rows -> 0.25ms; 3-token -> ~0 rows -> 0.19ms. The engine FTS SQL is UNBOUNDED (no LIMIT, ORDER BY write_cursor) so it scans the posting list, bm25-scores, and materializes EVERY matched row. Query-time porter stemming is one stem/token = negligible (free at engine level per Q2b). Only real query-path lever = bounding matched-row materialization (dormant FATHOMDB_PERF_SEARCH_LIMIT at lib.rs:3912) — a recall-affecting semantic change, OUT OF SCOPE. Secondary: engine adds ~17ms p50 @100k over raw FTS (reader-pool + dedup-on-body + SearchHit materialization), also growing with matched rows, but tokenizer-independent.",
dev/plans/runs/0.8.0-slice-6-output.json:43:    "ii_lighten_tokenizer": "REJECT — ~0ms latency gain (Q2a/Q2b) and -3/8 FTS recall (Q2c); wrong lever",
dev/plans/runs/0.8.0-slice-6-output.json:46:    "v_bound_result_set": "ORTHOGONAL/SEPARATE — top-k LIMIT on the text branch would MEET (not tier) the 100k budget but changes recall semantics; out of scope for B2, needs a dedicated retrieval ADR"
dev/plans/runs/0.8.0-slice-6-output.json:55:  "next_step_for_orchestrator": "Route the recommendation + HITL fork to the human. On HITL sign-off of option (i): author Slice 7 to tier AC-012 (mint AC-076 mirroring ac_013's AC013_GATE_N=10_000 branch in perf_gates.rs; supersede the unconditional 100k assert; keep porter tokenizer). Fold the 10k-tier ac_012 assertion + eu7 recall onto the canonical x86_64 runner in the Slice-40 re-scope (B2 + B1 + Q3 together) so the gate actually runs per-push (the META gap). Then re-run Slice 40 Phase A. Reap the slice-6 worktree (/tmp/fdb-slice-6-20260607T003001Z) per orchestration.md §11. IMPORTANT for the orchestrator's board update: the Slice-40 output.json B2 root-cause ('porter stemmer + diacritics folding materially more expensive at query time') is now MEASURED-FALSE — correct the board's B2 framing to 'O(N) corpus-scaling latency; ac_012 never tiered'."
