dev/plans/runs/0.8.2-pwrfix-output.json:38:    "note": "P(GO) asymptotes to ~0.44-0.50 regardless of N when lift=threshold=0.04. Root cause: decide() has two conjunctive gates — (1) f1_delta >= MATERIAL_F1_LIFT (point-estimate gate) AND (2) f1_ci_low > 0 (CI gate). The MDE<lift criterion ensures gate-2 has 80% power, but gate-1 fires only ~50% of the time when the TRUE effect exactly equals the threshold. N-sweep confirms (N=200..10000): P(GO) stays in [0.43, 0.46]. Study is underpowered at the aligned target."
dev/plans/runs/0.8.2-pwrfix-output.json:44:    "design mde-power-plan frozen field: flat-positive +0.03->+0.04 (2 occurrences), 'P(GO)>=0.8 under flat-positive +0.04 at N=1165, MDE~0.037<0.04', AMENDED 2026-06-19 on header",
dev/plans/runs/0.8.2-pwrfix-output.json:49:      "id": "study-underpowered-at-aligned-target",
dev/plans/runs/0.8.2-pwrfix-output.json:50:      "description": "P(GO) at N=1165, flat-positive +0.04, sd~0.445, rho=0.5 is ~0.45, not >=0.8. The code fix (FLAT_POSITIVE_LIFT = MATERIAL_F1_LIFT) is correct alignment, but reveals a fundamental design inconsistency: when lift=threshold, the point-estimate gate in decide() (f1_delta >= MATERIAL_F1_LIFT) caps P(GO) at ~50% regardless of N. The 'MDE<lift => 80% power' claim addresses only the CI-excludes-zero gate, not the point-estimate gate. In rev1 (threshold=0.02, lift=0.03), lift > threshold gave high P(gate-1), making the overall P(GO) high. Rev2 raised both to 0.04 (correct alignment) but inherits the problem that lift=threshold means P(GO)~50%.",
dev/plans/runs/0.8.2-pwrfix-output.json:51:      "resolution": "ESCALATE TO HITL — do NOT merge. HITL must choose one of: (A) set FLAT_POSITIVE_LIFT to the 'expected alternative' (e.g., 0.06 = 1.5x threshold, giving P(GO)>>0.8 at N=1165); (B) re-derive the required N for the lift=threshold case; or (C) redefine power_ok to condition on 'f1_delta>=threshold' (conditional power). Code changes on this branch are correct; only the lift/power-target design choice needs HITL."
dev/plans/runs/0.8.2-pwrfix-output.json:58:  "agent_verify_result": "fail — P(GO)@N=1165/flat-positive+0.04 = 0.45 < 0.80 (target); study is underpowered at the aligned target. All 44 tests green, pyright 0/0, tripwire clean. Code alignment is correct. ESCALATION REQUIRED before merge.",
dev/plans/runs/0.8.2-pwrfix-output.json:60:  "next_step_for_orchestrator": "ESCALATION: study underpowered at N=1165/+0.04 — P(GO)~0.45, not >=0.8. Code fixes (FLAT_POSITIVE_LIFT=MATERIAL_F1_LIFT, 3 test fixes, 2 new invariant tests, design doc mde-power-plan +0.03->+0.04) are correct and committed on branch (495b1aa9). All 44 tests green. Do NOT merge to main until HITL rules on the lift-vs-threshold split. Root cause: decide() gate-1 (f1_delta>=threshold) caps P(GO) at ~50% when lift=threshold exactly; the MDE<lift criterion ensures the CI gate has 80% power but does not address the point-estimate gate. HITL options: (A) set FLAT_POSITIVE_LIFT above threshold (e.g. 0.06='expected alternative' for 1.5x MDE ratio), (B) re-derive required N for lift=threshold power calculation, or (C) redefine power_ok to use conditional power. This is a design-level decision, not an implementer decision."
