dev/plans/runs/fathomdb-next-steps-codex-confirmation-run2.md:17:This is the highest-leverage first move because dense retrieval is already central to exploratory recall and multi-hop QA, but the observed system has a production/eval mismatch: production uses Mean pooling while the eval harness used CLS pooling, and CLS is the model-correct pooling for bge-small.
dev/plans/runs/fathomdb-next-steps-codex-confirmation-run2.md:46:- Cross-encoder: EVAL-ONLY until it beats the default path under the QA and recall bars.
dev/plans/runs/fathomdb-next-steps-codex-confirmation-run2.md:50:- Best agentic memory: LongMemEval recall and answer accuracy.
dev/plans/runs/fathomdb-next-steps-codex-confirmation-run2.md:51:- Exploratory recall: dense and fused IR relevance.
dev/plans/runs/fathomdb-next-steps-codex-confirmation-run2.md:52:- Deep-exploratory recall: hard queries where dense rank matters.
dev/plans/runs/fathomdb-next-steps-codex-confirmation-run2.md:61:- **eu7 ANN fidelity:** pass the hard floor with margin: full 7,667-query vector-stage recall@10 must be `>= 0.900`, compared with the measured `0.8960` full-corpus point and CI `[0.8640, 0.9250]` (§2.1). Prefer CI lower bound `>= 0.900` before treating the quantized store as robust.
dev/plans/runs/fathomdb-next-steps-codex-confirmation-run2.md:62:- **Agentic memory recall:** LongMemEval pooled R@10 must beat the best measured N=160 baseline, naive BM25 `0.625`, by at least `+0.04`, so bar `>= 0.665` (§3.1).
dev/plans/runs/fathomdb-next-steps-codex-confirmation-run2.md:63:- **Agentic memory answer accuracy:** answer accuracy should beat the best measured N=160 overall baseline, naive BM25 `0.406`, by at least `+0.04`, so bar `>= 0.446` (§3.2).
dev/plans/runs/fathomdb-next-steps-codex-confirmation-run2.md:65:- **MuSiQue >=3-hop QA:** do not require a formal GO on the existing rule at this stage because the decision rule was observed to be underpowered. Require point-estimate F1 no worse than passage dense `0.4866` and at least `+0.04` over fused `0.4502`, so bar `>= 0.4902` on pooled >=3-hop (§4.7).
dev/plans/runs/fathomdb-next-steps-codex-confirmation-run2.md:118:- Best agentic memory: extracted facts and temporal markers should help factoid, knowledge-update, multi-session, and temporal recall.
dev/plans/runs/fathomdb-next-steps-codex-confirmation-run2.md:119:- Exploratory recall: aliases/facts add lexical handles for documents dense may miss.
dev/plans/runs/fathomdb-next-steps-codex-confirmation-run2.md:120:- Deep-exploratory recall: bridge-diverse evidence selection targets hard discrimination.
dev/plans/runs/fathomdb-next-steps-codex-confirmation-run2.md:128:- **Pooled >=3-hop QA:** only run priced answerer after bridge bar passes. Require point-estimate F1 `>= 0.5266`, which is `+0.04` over the strongest measured full-run arm, passage_dense `0.4866` (§4.7). Because the decision rule was underpowered, treat CI lower bound as directional rather than a hard GO gate for this step; require no large regression signal, e.g. CI lower not below `-0.02` versus passage_dense.
