dev/plans/runs/fathomdb-next-steps-codex-hypothesis.md:13:The live opportunity is D1/D2. Passage-dense deserves a registered comparison because it beat fused on MuSiQue pooled ≥3-hop F1, `0.4866` vs `0.4502` (§4.7), despite fused remaining the registered comparator. For memory recall, current fused retrieval does not beat BM25: LongMemEval pooled R@10 was BM25 `0.625`, fused `0.606`, FTS-only `0.562` (§3.1). Enrichment is weak but plausible only if scaled and controlled: N=40 FTS-enriched `0.775` trailed FTS-only `0.800`, while placebo was `0.700` (§3.4); lower BM25 `b` improved plain/enriched behavior up to `0.75`/`0.775` at `b=0.00` (§3.5). The IR corpus remains bounded by eu7/eu8: production vector fidelity was `0.8960` on N=7,667, below the `0.90` floor (§2.1), and report-only IR relevance recall@10 was `0.571` (§2.2).
dev/plans/runs/fathomdb-next-steps-codex-hypothesis.md:49:- Exploratory recall: directly targets eu8 relevance recall@10 ceiling `0.571` (§2.2) while preserving eu7.
dev/plans/runs/fathomdb-next-steps-codex-hypothesis.md:50:- Deep-exploratory recall: PRF is the cheapest deterministic way to pull deeper semantically related candidates from the hard subset without LLM calls.
dev/plans/runs/fathomdb-next-steps-codex-hypothesis.md:55:- eu7 fidelity: must pass `>=0.90` recall@10. Current N=7,667 vector-stage value was `0.8960`, CI `[0.8640, 0.9250]` (§2.1), so the repaired dense path must clear the hard floor before product promotion.
dev/plans/runs/fathomdb-next-steps-codex-hypothesis.md:56:- eu8 relevance: report recall@10 against the frozen IR qrels; require no regression from `0.571` (§2.2), and target `>=0.59` as a practical first lift. Also report the hard deep-exploratory subset separately; require a positive recall@10 and recall@50 movement, with no eu7 regression.
dev/plans/runs/fathomdb-next-steps-codex-hypothesis.md:57:- LongMemEval: run recall@10/@20 and per-class factoid, knowledge_update, multi_session, temporal. Minimum bar: fused/PRF must beat BM25 R@10 `0.625` and R@20 `0.694` from §3.1, and must not lose the multi_session signal where fused was `0.325` vs BM25 `0.275` (§3.1).
dev/plans/runs/fathomdb-next-steps-codex-hypothesis.md:58:- MuSiQue: registered pooled ≥3-hop dF1 vs fused-RRF `k=60`; GO only if ΔF1 `>=0.04` and paired-bootstrap CI lower bound `>0`, with the existing trend/EM/confident-wrong/power gates. Baseline fused is `0.4502`, passage_dense `0.4866`, and ppr_fusion `0.4097` (§4.7). Because the M1 rule was underpowered even at N=1165 per the appendix, run cheap validation, power simulation, then HITL approve any priced full pass.
dev/plans/runs/fathomdb-next-steps-codex-hypothesis.md:103:- Exploratory recall: adds deterministic sparse recall for concepts that dense misses.
dev/plans/runs/fathomdb-next-steps-codex-hypothesis.md:104:- Deep-exploratory recall: gives hard queries more discriminative lexical handles without graph BFS/PPR.
dev/plans/runs/fathomdb-next-steps-codex-hypothesis.md:113:- QA reader cost/power: use cheap-validate first; do not treat N=300 as decisive if the power simulation says the registered rule is underpowered.
dev/plans/runs/fathomdb-next-steps-codex-hypothesis.md:117:D2 depends on Step 1 because enrichment should be tested against the repaired dense/fused baseline, not against a known-bug production dense path. It also needs Step 1's candidate logging and bridge diagnostics so enrichment is judged by bridge presence, placebo-controlled recall, and final answer F1 rather than by a single optimistic recall number.
