dev/plans/runs/0.8.0-slice-40-ga2-codex-review-20260608T150000Z.md:4072:  When EU7 writes the release measurement JSON, this field is named `recall_at_10_fused_search_delta` but stores `rec.fused_mean` rather than the delta between vector-stage and fused recall. In runs where vector recall is ~0.937 and fused recall is ~0.871, consumers of this artifact will read `0.871` as the delta instead of the actual ~`0.066`, which makes the GA-2 evidence misleading; either rename the field/log label or store `rec.mean - rec.fused_mean`.
dev/plans/runs/0.8.0-slice-40-ga2-codex-review-20260608T150000Z.md:4073:The code and tests largely hold together, but the new release measurement output mislabels fused recall as a delta, which can mislead downstream GA evidence.
dev/plans/runs/0.8.0-slice-40-ga2-codex-review-20260608T150000Z.md:4077:- [P3] Report the actual fused recall delta — /tmp/fdb-ga2-20260608T145205Z/src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/tests/eu7_real_corpus_ac.rs:896-896
dev/plans/runs/0.8.0-slice-40-ga2-codex-review-20260608T150000Z.md:4078:  When EU7 writes the release measurement JSON, this field is named `recall_at_10_fused_search_delta` but stores `rec.fused_mean` rather than the delta between vector-stage and fused recall. In runs where vector recall is ~0.937 and fused recall is ~0.871, consumers of this artifact will read `0.871` as the delta instead of the actual ~`0.066`, which makes the GA-2 evidence misleading; either rename the field/log label or store `rec.mean - rec.fused_mean`.
